                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre and irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (brilliant scarlet, strong amaranth, strong
                           vermillion).</seg>
                        <date>Mid 18th - early 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Rubrication of the main text is executed in
                           brilliant red. 
 Nomina sacra; names of the original donors (but
                           mostly erased); incipit of sections and subsections; word mǝʿrāf (fol.
                           109rb); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 Names of other donors, added (later) in a secondary hand,
                           are written in strong amaranth and strong vermillion.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting tends to left-sloping;
                        it appears very irregular due to the variations in ruling (the size of the
                        columns and the space between lines often differs significantly: e.g.,
                           <locus target="#23v">23v</locus>, 89rv, 92r, 100r), changes of the pen
                        nib (slender or broad nib: e.g. <locus target="#32v">32v</locus> against
                        33r, 83v against 84; within one column: e.g., <locus target="#29rb">29rb</locus>, 32ra, 37vb, 102ra), changes in letters' height, and
                        varying spaces between the
                        letters.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes in the upper margins in a secondary hand, in
                              pencil, indicating the readings for church feasts and other occasions:
                              fols. 91ra, 92ra, 93ra, 93va, 95vb.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>The name(s) of the original donor(s), mentioned throughout the Ms., have been erased and partly replaced with other names in a secondary hand. </desc>
                        </item> 
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>Omissions inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 3vb, 27vb, 38va, 99ra. </desc>
                        </item> 
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>Corrections written over erased words: e.g., fols. 12vb, 39vb, 43va, 54ra, 99ra. </desc>
                        </item> 
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>Immediate corrections indicated by a line encircling the words: fols. 30rb, 34rb. </desc>
                        </item> 
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>Most of the erasures are marked with parallel lines: <locus target="#71vb">fol.  71vb</locus>. </desc>
                        </item> 
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <desc>Trinitarian formula: <locus target="#108vb">fol.  108vb</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
